HEADWORD: Gladstone
<hw>Glad"stone</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Named after Wm. E.
<ets>Gladstone</ets>.]</ety> <def>A four-wheeled pleasure carriage with
two inside seats, calash top, and seats for driver and
footman.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

